column2: With the growing concern about COVID-19 and FWD's continuing commitment to care for customers, FWD is providing existing plan holders ‚ÄúFWD COVID-19 Ready,‚Äù an additional lump sum medical and funeral benefit if diagnosed with COVID-19, at no extra cost. In addition, for customers who are diagnosed with COVID-19, FWD will be extending payment grace period to 90 days and releasing the FWD COVI...D-19 Ready medical benefit claims within 48 hours. Ask your financial advisor for details or contact our 24/7 LiveChat at fwd.com.ph and on our mobile app, FWD Tapp. Learn more at bit.ly/FWDCOVID19Ready Benefit is available for active and eligible life insurance plans issued up to Feb 29, 2020, except group insurance plans, KanDuu (KanMend, KanLive, and KanGuard), Set Ka Na, and Peace. column2: With the growing concern about COVID-19 and FWD's continuing commitment to care for customers, FWD is providing existing plan holders ‚ÄúFWD COVID-19 Ready,‚Äù  an additional lump sum medical and funeral benefit if diagnosed with COVID-19, at no extra cost. This benefit is provided on top of eligible and active FWD insurance plans and riders. In addition, for customers who are diagnosed with COVID-19, FWD will be extending payment grace period to 90 days and releasing the FWD COV...ID-19 Ready medical benefit claims within 48 hours. Ask your financial advisor for details or contact our 24/7 LiveChat at fwd.com.ph and on our mobile app, FWD Tapp. Learn more at bit.ly/FWDCOVID19Ready Benefit is available for active and eligible life insurance plans issued up to Feb 29, 2020, except group insurance plans, KanDuu (KanMend, KanLive, and KanGuard), Set Ka Na, and Peace. Coverage period until April 15. #FWDCOVID19Ready

column2: At FWD, our vision is to change the way people feel about insurance. We listen to you and work tirelessly to redefine insurance through your eyes.  When we assist you, we go above and beyond to put ourselves in your shoes first.  We want to give you the protection you need through easy-to-understand products, supported by digital technology. We focus on your other needs as much as your financial ones. We continue to innovate to provide you the best service‚Äîquick, easy, and hassle-free.    We‚Äôre here for you when you need us. We became the first insurance company in the Philippines to offer 24/7 customer service and launched Tapp, our one-tap insurance app, that allows you to manage your plans at the touch of your fingers. We want you to celebrate living without fear because we always have your back.

Driving in the Philippines means you‚Äôll spend countless hours stuck in heavy traffic. It‚Äôs the reality. With this, always assume that most people are in a sour mood already and their patience is wearing thin by the minute. Refrain from doing anything aggressive that will only add fuel to the fire. Maintain the proper speed and observe adequate space for lane changes. If a motorist is tailgating you, move over and let them go. Remember: It isn‚Äôt worth causing an accident or serious injury, just to prove you‚Äôre right. If you expect disciplined driving from others, start with yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive

column2: If you‚Äôre trying to stick to a budget, it‚Äôs better to shop without the direct or indirect influence (aka peer pressure) from others. column2: Your vehicle‚Äôs horn should only be used when necessary and not just because you want to make noise and express annoyance to another motorist. If you can help it, don‚Äôt show displeasure to other drivers, minimizing the risk of getting into an altercation or road rage accident. No matter how many times you press your horn, it will not make traffic go faster, so best to have your hands useful on the wheel or gear stick. Listen to music or even meditate to calm yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive
